  "prompt": "What is the procedure of getting admission into IIT for NRIs?",
  "response": "Admission to the Indian Institutes of Technology (IITs) for Non-Resident Indians (NRIs) can be done through the following procedures:\n\n### 1. **Understanding Eligibility Criteria:**\n   - NRIs must have completed their schooling (10+2) with Physics, Chemistry, and Mathematics (PCM) as subjects.\n   - They should qualify for the Joint Entrance Examination (JEE) Advanced, which is required for admission to IITs.\n\n### 2. **Qualifying for JEE:**\n   - **JEE Main:** NRIs must first appear for the JEE Main examination, which is conducted by the National Testing Agency (NTA). \n   - **JEE Advanced:** Only the top students from the JEE Main are eligible to appear for JEE Advanced, which is necessary for admission to IITs.\n\n### 3. **Direct Admission Scheme for NRIs:**\n   - IITs also have a provision for admitting a certain percentage of NRI students directly, bypassing the JEE requirements, based on their performance in qualifying examinations. Check the specific IIT's website for the latest information on this.\n\n### 4. **Application Process:**\n   - **Registration:** NRIs need to register for JEE Main through the official website. They will need to provide personal and academic details.\n   - **Obtaining a Registration Number:** After registration, they will receive a unique registration number.\n\n### 5. **Examinations:**\n   - Appear for JEE Main and, if eligible, JEE Advanced.\n   - Ensure to meet the cut-off scores for both examinations to advance to the admission stages.\n\n### 6. **Counseling and Seat Allocation:**\n   - After qualifying JEE Advanced, NRIs must participate in the Joint Seat Allocation Authority (JoSAA) counseling process.\n   - They can select their preferred courses and IITs based on their JEE Advanced rank.\n\n### 7. **Document Verification:**\n   - Ensure to have the necessary documents ready for verification, including:\n     - Mark sheets of 10th and 12th standard\n     - Passport and visa\n     - Other relevant certificates\n  \n### 8. **Payment of Fees:**\n   - Upon allocation of a seat, an admission fee must be paid to secure the seat.\n   - NRI students usually have to pay a higher tuition fee compared to Indian citizens.\n\n### 9. **Final Admission:**\n   - After payment and document verification, the candidate will be admitted to the selected program at the IIT.\n\n### 10. **Stay Updated:**\n   - Admission procedures and rules may change, so it's advisable for NRIs to frequently check the official IIT and JEE websites for the latest information.\n\nBe sure to pay attention to deadlines and specific criteria for each IIT, as these can vary.",
